GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 823
Short Title: Safe Steps for Greenville Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Smith (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
April 23, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO APPROPRIATE FUNDS FOR CITY OF GREENVILLE PEDESTRIAN SAFETY
3 IMPROVEMENTS.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. There is appropriated from the Highway Fund to the Department of
6 Transportation the sum of five million dollars ($5,000,000) in nonrecurring funds for the
7 2026-2027 fiscal year to be allocated to the City of Greenville for pedestrian safety
8 improvements.
9 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective July 1, 2026.
*S823-v-1*

